            <prj:justificationText>As for gal1, we estimated the flux in the [CII] 158 um line (CII 2P3/2 2P1/2) for VVDS-J022711.25-043247.5 (gal2) by using the equivalent width of the [CII] 1334.5 angstrom absorption line detected in the VVDS survey. We obtained a value for the integrated flux of 2.36 +/- 1.41 Jy km/s, where the errors are here taken at the 95% confidence level (2 sigma). The diameter of the source in [CII] 158 um emission is 0.8", as indicated by the CFHT photometry. At the spatial resolution of 0.14", this leads to an average integrated flux per synthesized beam of 0.16 +/- 0.09 Jy km/s.

