The integration time is calculated from the central fiducial value of the peak intensity, i.e. 2.6 mJy, by requiring that in each spatial resolution element the (average) line is detected at a signal-to-noise ratio S/N=7. Hence, a sensitivity of 0.37 mJy and a total integration time of 2.35 hr (1.29 h on source). This condition implies that, even if the real CII flux is at -2 sigma from the central value (i.e. 1.0 mJy), we would be able to detect the source at a S/N~3, still a good value to derive a reliable kinematics. With such a sensitivity, we have a probability of 97% that the source is detected at S/N&gt;3 in each resolution element and a 50% probability that the S/N is equal or larger than 7.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
